== Curry ==

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and
mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}(minced or grated). Trim and slice
@button mushrooms{4%ounce}(sliced, or pre-sliced). Peel and dice
@potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Roughly chop @cashews{1/2%ounce}(roughly
chopped).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add half the onion, @ginger{1/2%tsp}(minced), and a large pinch of
@salt{pinch}; cook, stirring, until deeply browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add mushrooms, potatoes, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and as many
@chili flakes{1/2%tsp} as you like; cook, stirring, ~{5%minutes} more.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @garam masala{1%tsp},
@water{3/4%cup}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}; bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce to a
low simmer, cover, and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if necessary. Remove from heat.

== Pea-Studded Rice ==

While curry cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and cook, stirring, until softened and
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in @peas{4%oz}(frozen), cashews, and a drizzle
of oil. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Assembly ==

> Reserve any remaining coconut milk for another use.

Stir @coconut milk{2%tbsp} into curry.

Divide pea-studded rice between #bowls{}; top with curry to one side. Serve.

 